text_a: Alex needed groceries. She made a list of things to buy. She gathered her reusable canvas sacks. She walked to the store.

text_a: Our kids went to parochial school. The school made the parents work at functions. In December, I had to sell cookies at the school Christmas Bazaar. I sat in a room in the school and took money in.

text_a: Jamie had sprained her ankle. Her friends were going to the fair. Jamie wanted to go to the fair with her friends. Her mother bought her a set of crutches.

text_a: One day after school some of my friends were talking to an old friend. I didn't know who she was, so they introduced us. She had gone to grade school with them, but not our high school. That summer she became part of our group, so we hung out a lot.
text_b_pos: We ended up falling in love and eventually got married.

text_b_pos: Eve thought the couch was very comfortable.
text_b_neg: She bought a new couch to replace it.

text_a: My favorite animal is the Arabian Oryx. I can't usually see them because it's an African antelope. I have to go to zoos. My family bought me a nice present for my birthday this year.

text_b_pos: Robbie and I dressed up for the occasion.

text_a: Kelly was reading about hybrid animals online. And she saw pictures of ligers. She was impressed by their size and strength. But she wondered if they could live in the wild.

text_b_pos: Haley decided to use the money to buy gifts for her family.
text_b_neg: One night she decided to cut her own hair.

text_a: Driving home from work the other day I got a flat tire. It was rainy and cold out. I could have called the towing company but chose not to. Instead I changed the tire myself.
text_b_pos: I was miserable but saved a ton.
text_b_neg: I was miserable that he had fun.

text_a: Lee recently just got a new job. Today is her first day. Lee is very nervous as she gets ready to go to work. Lee drives to work and listens to music to relax.
text_b_pos: Lee arrives at her new job and everyone is very welcoming.

text_b_pos: Kev decided not to come hunting.
text_b_neg: Kev was excited to try out his new gun.

text_a: The man got greedy. He took what wasn't his. His friends noticed the behavior. They asked the man to change.

text_b_neg: We then sat down and began to count the cars,

text_b_pos: The next pitch he hit a homerun.

text_a: Gina is an avid reader. She last read Moby Dick. However, Gina really hates some of the books that she's read. Moby Dick is one of them.

text_b_pos: Jenny paid for the order of the person behind her.
text_b_neg: Jenny paid for her coffee with cash.

text_a: Mike used to play racketball with Perry. They would reserve a court a couple times a week. But one time Mike hit Perry by accident in the back of the head. Perry was not very happy about that.
text_b_pos: Mike had to apologize.
text_b_neg: Mike and Perry got married.
